{"ticker": "TEM", "company": "Tempus AI", "weight_sum": 19.580000000000002, "etfs": ["ARKVX", "ARKG", "ARKK", "ARKUX", "ARKSX"], "is_private": false, "query": "($TEM OR \"Tempus AI\") -is:retweet min_faves:10 since_time:1777928214 until_time:1777935414", "n_fetched": 8, "n_kept": 3, "n_dropped": 5, "kept": [{"type": "tweet", "id": "2051271622200275393", "url": "https://x.com/AuditTheHerd/status/2051271622200275393", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/AuditTheHerd/status/2051271622200275393", "text": "$TEM reports earnings on Tuesday, and there\u2019s quite a bit to consider since the last print. \n\nYou would never know based on price action but since Q4 2025, Tempus has made meaningful progress across several fronts:\n\nMerck partnership - Expanded its oncology collaboration to scale their AI enabled clinical trial matching and real world data insights\n\nPredicta Biosciences agreement - Entered a new partnership to advance AI diagnostics in early cancer detection\n\nTIME recognition- Named one of TIME\u2019s 10 Most Influential Health & Life Science Companies of 2026. Nothing that will impact #s but great for publicity and recruiting. \n\nMore institutional interest -41 hedge funds held $TEM at the end of Q4, up from 32 the previous quarter\n\nTurning to Q1: Street expectations sit around $345M in revenue, up \u223c35% YoY with EPS still expected to be negative, in the -$0.20 to -$0.52 range.\n\nI will not be making any predictions on rev or eps numbers as it is still early in the story\u2026.\n\n**What I\u2019ll be paying attention to on the call:**\n\n- **Oncology test volumes**: Can the company maintain 35%+ growth, and what are they seeing on reimbursement trends?\n- **MRD adoption**: Minimal residual disease is a large new market. I\u2019m curious whether we\u2019ll see signs of early traction in Q1. \n- **Data business**: AI and data licensing are high margin but tend to be lumpy. The question is whether pharma budgets held steady\n- **Partnership monetization**: How quickly will the Merck and Predicta deals begin contributing to revenue?\n- **FY26 guidance**: Management previously outlined \u223c$1.59B, or \u223c25% growth. Reaffirming that, with a credible path to EBITDA profitability, would be important for sentiment\n\nTone and clarity on guidance will likely matter more to the stock than whether EPS beats by a few cents.\n\nFor those who don\u2019t know, there is also an investor day on May 29th. Screenshot below.", "source": "Twitter for iPhone", "retweetCount": 0, "replyCount": 6, "likeCount": 27, "quoteCount": 0, "viewCount": 1206, "createdAt": "Mon May 04 12:04:00 +0000 2026", "lang": "en", "bookmarkCount": 5, "isReply": false, "inReplyToId": null, "conversationId": "2051271622200275393", "displayTextRange": [0, 280], "inReplyToUserId": null, "inReplyToUsername": null, "author": {"type": "user", "userName": "AuditTheHerd", "url": "https://x.com/AuditTheHerd", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/AuditTheHerd", "id": "2001724228165603331", "name": "Audit The Herd", "isVerified": false, "isBlueVerified": true, "verifiedType": null, "profilePicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_images/2009656638802673664/r8l42ol-_normal.jpg", "coverPicture": "https://pbs.twimg.com/profile_banners/2001724228165603331/1768601479", "description": "", "location": "", "followers": 3472, "following": 61, "status": "", "canDm": true, "canMediaTag": true, "createdAt": "Thu Dec 18 18:40:28 +0000 2025", "entities": {"description": {"urls": []}, "url": {}}, "fastFollowersCount": 0, "favouritesCount": 4588, "hasCustomTimelines": true, "isTranslator": false, "mediaCount": 150, "statusesCount": 1491, "withheldInCountries": [], "affiliatesHighlightedLabel": {}, "possiblySensitive": false, "pinnedTweetIds": ["2010039308531708393"], "profile_bio": {"description": "CPA working in corporate finance. Objective commentary on equities. Never financial advice.", "entities": {"description": {}, "url": {"urls": [{"display_url": "open.substack.com/pub/is