rgical) \u2014 da Vinci robotics with AI upgrades. Record procedure growth.\n4. $GEHC (GE HealthCare) \u2014 AI imaging, ultrasound & diagnostics. Hospital AI upgrade cycle is just starting.\n5. $SYK (Stryker) \u2014 AI in orthopedics, surgical navigation & robotics. Strong MedTech AI play.\n6. $MDT (Medtronic) \u2014 AI-driven diabetes, cardiac monitoring & surgical tech.\n7. $LLY (Eli Lilly) \u2014 AI across drug development + blockbuster GLP-1 drugs. Defensive + growth.\n8. $SDGR (Schr\u00f6dinger) \u2014 Physics-based AI platform for drug design. High-upside software play.\n9. $HIMS (Hims & Hers) \u2014 Telehealth + AI personalization. Explosive growth at attractive valuation.\n10. $MRVL \u2014 High-speed connectivity powering AI data centers that healthcare AI needs.\n\nMy observation:  \nWhile everyone chases consumer AI, the real money will be made in AI + Healthcare \u2014 saving lives and slashing costs. Most of these names are still undervalued relative to the transformation they\u2019re driving.\n\nKey catalysts ahead:\n\u2022 More FDA AI device approvals\n\u2022 Hospital CapEx rebound in robotics & imaging\n\u2022 Breakthroughs in AI drug discovery (faster & cheaper pipelines)\n\nThis is the next leg of the AI boom \u2014 from chatbots to curing diseases.\n\nWhich AI healthcare stock are you watching or holding? Drop your top pick \ud83d\udc47", "source": "Twitter for iPhone", "retweetCount": 18, "replyCount": 10, "likeCount": 41, "quoteCount": 0, "viewCount": 257, "createdAt": "Mon May 04 17:46:16 +0000 2026", "lang": "en", "bookmarkCount": 16, "isReply": false, "inReplyToId": null, "conversationId": "2051357759149670567", "displayTextRange": [0, 283], "inReplyToUserId": null, "inReplyToUsername": null, "author": {"type": "user", "userName": "2wayWatson", "url": "https://x.com/2wayWatson", "twitterUrl": "https://twitter.com/2wayWatson", "id": "1734319969859416064", "name": "Wall Street Cowboy", "isVerified": false, "isBlueVerified": true, "verifiedType"